The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Thursday, November 07, 2002 				 Bangla quartet injured in accident
																								Dhaka: Four members of Bangladeshs national cricket team were injured when their taxi overturned on Wednesday, an official said.																								The Bangladesh Cricket Board official said the vehicle flipped over while trying to avert a collision with a truck in the capitals Dhanmandi area.																								Batsman Alok Kapali and Tushar Imran were given first aid, but Tapash Baishya and Rafiqul Islam Khan were hospitalised, the official said.																								The injuries do not seem to be serious, but doctors are making sure and they were thus hospitalised, the official said.																								Bangladesh has one of the highest death tolls in road accidents in south Asia. 																								Pollocks plan																								South African captain Shaun Pollock could forfeit his opening role in the first Test against Sri Lanka starting Friday, adds a report from Johannesburg. The selectors want to do some experiments with the new ball bowlers. (AGENCIES)
